 <h3>Community Information</h3>

<p>Located in the heart of Southern California between Los Angeles and San Bernardino,
Ontario, CA has been known as a "Model Community" since its earliest days. Ontario's
excellent position allows for easy access to some of its destination hot spots, such as the
nearby San Gabriel Mountains, famous Orange County beaches, major attractions such
as Disneyland and the annual Tournament of Roses Parade, all alongside this bustling
community, full of life. Ontario is full of fun activities, ranging from shopping at local malls,
visiting art and photography museums, top-notch restaurants and amusement parks to
golfing. It is also fun to explore outside the county and seeing the Aquarium of the Pacific,
zoos and Big Bear Lake! With a Metrolink train and public bus transportation, your options
for travelling and adventure are never limited!</p>
